  "texts": [
    "Still, traditional screening methods rely on manual interpretation of OCT images and visual field tests by trained specialists, which can be time-consuming and subject to inter-observer variability (23).",
    "AI, particularly CNNs, has demonstrated potential in automating the analysis of these tests for glaucoma detection and progression monitoring (24).",
    "Several studies have developed and validated CNN models for glaucoma detection using OCT images.",
    "trained a CNN on 48,116 OCT images and achieved an AUC of 0.986 for detecting glaucoma, with a sensitivity of 95.6% and a specificity of 92.0% (25).",
    "The model's performance was comparable to that of glaucoma specialists, suggesting that AI could replace human graders in glaucoma screening."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Still, traditional screening methods rely on manual interpretation of OCT images and visual field tests by trained specialists, which can be time-consuming and subject to inter-observer variability (23).",
